Step 2 - System Requirements (SRS)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Project Objectives

✅ Build an 8-pad MIDI Octapad
✅ Detect drum hits accurately
✅ Calculate hit velocity
✅ Send USB MIDI messages
✅ Work on Windows, macOS and Linux
✅ Low latency
✅ Stable firmware


3. System Scope

✔ 8 Drum Pads
✔ Piezo Sensors
✔ ESP32-S3
✔ USB MIDI
✔ Velocity Detection
✔ Laptop Connection
✔ MIDI Note Mapping
✔ Threshold Adjustment (Firmware)
✔ Sensitivity Adjustment (Firmware)


4. Functional Requirements

FR-01 - The system shall detect hits on every pad.
FR-02 - The system shall determine which pad was struck.
FR-03 - The system shall calculate hit velocity.
FR-04 - The system shall convert the hit into a MIDI Note On message.
FR-05 - The system shall transmit MIDI over USB.
FR-06 - The system shall send MIDI Note Off automatically.
FR-07 - Each pad shall have its own MIDI note.

Example:

Pad	MIDI Note
1	36
2	38
3	42
4	46
5	49
6	51
7	48
8	43
FR-08 - The system shall continuously scan all pads.
FR-09 - The firmware shall ignore electrical noise.
FR-10 - The system shall operate continuously without restarting.


5. Non-Functional Requirements

Performance
  Latency < 10 ms (target)
  Fast response
  Smooth playing

Reliability
  No random notes
  Stable USB connection
  Stable firmware

Maintainability
  Modular code
  Easy debugging
  Easy updates

Portability
  Must work on: Windows / macOS / Linux


